==Commercial products==
ST Kinetics started on the commercial vehicle business in 2004 and has yet to establish a presence in the global marketplace even though its subsidiaries are well-established brands within their respective countries.

===Construction Vehicles===
ST Kinetics' BZK JV in China produces fixed and articulated off-road dumptrucks ranging from 20 to 52 ton.  BZK also produces complementary products like cement carriers and mixers and terminal port tractors for container ports operation.  Jonyang excavators has been in operation in China and surrounding regions over 30 years.  These wheeled and tracked hydraulic excavators are also customisable to suit special conditions, such as operation in swampy areas and mini-excavators for smaller operations.  LeeBoy has been a producer of small, commercial asphalt pavers and grading products since 1964 and has maintained a leader within the U.S. market.

===Distribution Vehicles===
Both Hackney and Kidron are the respective market leaders in aluminium and refrigerated truck bodies in the U.S. respectively.  Hackney beverage trucks, with its optimised compartmentalisation and light-weight aluminium bodies, is able to provide low lifecycle cost to the operators.  Kidron pioneered multi-temperature distribution with its Adjustable Compartmentalised Multi-temperature System (ACMT) of movable partitions.  The ACMT allows easy configuration of loads requiring different temperature and compartment sizes.

===Urban & Emergency vehicles===
Hackney emergency vehicles are designed for high payloads and mobility in crisis and natural disaster situations, ranging from conventional fires and vehicle accidents to building collapses and hazardous materials containment and mitigation.  ST Kinetics also produces a series of Urban vehicles, such as [[ambulance]]s, [[HAZMAT]] vehicles, [[fire engines]], terminal prime movers for local use.  Customers include [[PSA International]], the [[Singapore Civil Defence Force]] and the [[Singapore Police Force]].

==Automotive Services==
The automotive services have continued since the SAE days to become the Total Support & Services arm of the present day ST Kinetics.  ST Kinetics continue to provide MRO services to military, commercial and general customers.

===MRO Services for Military Vehicles===
As part of the integrated logistics support system for the major platforms, ST Kinetics has established the MRO services under its Kinetics Integrated Services (KIS) arm.  KIS also provides maintenance of the existing SAF fleet of MAN trucks.

===Accident Repair & MRO for Commercial & Passenger Vehicles===
ST Kinetics' STAR Automotive Centre provides accident repair and general MRO for commercial and passenger vehicles.  In recent years, STAR has ventured into China and opened 3 centres in Hangzhou,  Guangzhou & Zhejiang.  

===Component Servicing===
SDDA is both Detroit Diesel and Allison transmission's Asia distribution centre as well as a service hub for the overhaul of automotive engines, Allison transmissions and fuel injection pumps, and the servicing of electrical, electronic & hydraulic components.

